pageContext.claim: “When I came in … we had an economy that was going down. You remember the numbers. They were terrible. And they were going down. We were going to be in negative numbers very soon. And now, we have numbers that are incredible. The economy is setting records.”
pageContext.analysis: Trump inherited an expanding economy from Obama and exaggerates the impact of his policies. The United States had added jobs for 76 straight months before Trump became president. In ways, the positive trends under Trump are only a continuation of an economic expansion that began in 2010.
